You have to use different format specifiers for printing floating points and integers.

Also, in `System.out.printf()`, you can separate the values using comma `,`. See [this](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/util/Formatter.html#syntax).

`%d` - for integers

`%f` - for floating points

`%.6f` - for floating points with 6 digits of precision


Also, I removed the extra nested for loop, it was unnecessary.

```
public static void main(String[] args) {
    for (int i = 0; i &lt;= 10; i++) {
        System.out.printf(&quot;%d %.6f %.6f %d %d\n&quot;, i, Math.cbrt(i), Math.sqrt(i), (i * i), (i * i * i));
    }
}
```

