The [parallel builds](https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/MAVEN/Parallel+builds+in+Maven+3) feature in Maven 3 is still in the experimental stages, and it appears that there are known issues with thread safety in the `plexus-utils` library prior to version 2.0.5 - you&#39;re using version 1.5.1.

**Edit:**

Your problem is this dependency:

            &lt;dependency&gt;
                &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.surefire&lt;/groupId&gt;
                &lt;artifactId&gt;surefire-junit47&lt;/artifactId&gt;
                &lt;version&gt;${testing.surefire.version}&lt;/version&gt;
            &lt;/dependency&gt;

[`surefire-junit47`](http://mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.apache.maven.surefire/surefire-junit47/2.17) depends on [`maven-surefire-common`](http://mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.apache.maven.surefire/maven-surefire-common/2.17), which in turn depends on [`maven-artifact`](http://mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.apache.maven/maven-artifact/2.0.9), which depends on `plexus-utils-1.5.1`. As stated above, this has known thread safety issues, which is likely what is causing your problems. I&#39;m not sure what parts of the `surefire-junit47` library you&#39;re using, but if switching to `surefire-junit4` is an option, then that should solve your problem.

After looking at the docs for the surefire plugin a little more, it looks like you need the `surefire-junit47` provider to run parallel tests. I&#39;d try overriding `plexus-utils` to be version 2.0.5 and see if that works; otherwise, you can override the `maven-artifact` version to 3.0.3 or higher and see if that works.

